Absolutely fantastic experience. City Jake was in front of the grill with freshly gelled hair, kitchen bib on, and white New Balance shoes ready for a big day.  Our orders were taken promptly and the coffee was in self serve pumpers ready to pump, when my bro asked about which flave he should try- City Jake barked “the jump start is no girly man coffee, it’s black euro”. We doubled down on his signature blend, and walked through the restaurant admiring City Jakes store-long shelves littered with Bass Fishing trophies and awards while the ambiance of a lit af grill was popping off in the background. My blueberry pancakes are an absolute 10/10 and City Jake himself suggested fresh whipped cream on the top, to which I couldn’t turn down in any lifetime. The four Midwesterners in my party noted more than once “wish we had city Jake in Kansas City.”  Thanks for the A+ service and food Jake. Here’s to many years of successful business and all the bass a man could ever catch.
